Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.24,0:00:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Praise\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.76,0:01:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,his song.\NGive me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.32,0:01:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet everybody this morning. Hi.\N>> Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.84,0:01:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi again.\N>> Everybody in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning.\NHey,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> look at the big guy back here.\N>> The big guy is hiding in the back. He
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.84,0:01:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't want to scare me up front.\N>> Big people like that scare me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.43,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Morning. How are you?\N>> Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.12,0:02:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,hello. Hi.\NHi, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.80,0:02:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well,\NI got to keep moving. It's hard to meet
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody, but we'll meet other people\Nafterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.31,0:03:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NGood morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Good morning.\N>> Yes, it is indeed. And uh I know we're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.64,0:03:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in for a good time today. I know it's\Ngoing to be really good cuz I was about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.40,0:03:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to greet doctor and he got out of the\Ncar saying I'm back in the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.51,0:03:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, I don't know what's coming, but\N>> we're back on the home court.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.40,0:03:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I always tell the homep cuz you all keep\Nshowing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.56,0:03:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it is my pleasure this morning to uh\Nintroduce again my friend, mentor and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:04:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,gift to the world and his right arm\NSusan, Dr. David Hman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.04,0:04:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.84,0:04:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were we?\NWe have to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to provide a contextualization\Nfor the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Devotional non-duality means the\Nstraight way to God bypassing the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.47,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the intellect, the ego.\N>> We're either not on or not on go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got so many wires on. I don't know\Nwhether I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.63,0:05:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,going to get electrocuted or what here.\N>> Are we on?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.03,0:05:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> First crisis of the day successfully\Ntranscended. Thank the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.28,0:05:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way you get by in today's\Nelectronic world, the way I get by is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the help of God. I look at all this\Nequipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.32,0:05:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we recontextualize the purpose of\Nall the lectures and the books and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.56,0:05:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nwhat we're really talking about is the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,direct way to God\Nby bypassing the mind, the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.68,0:06:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all positionalities,\Nall of our dedications to the ego and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all its rewards.\NYou either serve God or you serve the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,ego.\NThe way to the way to God is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,obscure.\NPeople worship all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.47,0:06:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If the way to God were easy, everybody\Nwould be enlightened. So this is a world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.08,0:06:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,dominated by the ego. To transcend the\Ngravity of the ego is extraordinarily
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult. In fact, without higher\Ntruth, it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.91,0:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one is dedicated to reaching the\Nhighest truth or one genulelex to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.72,0:06:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,ego and that decision is what\Nmakes the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.00,0:07:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in calibrated levels of truth. So,\NOn the calibrated levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.80,0:07:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness, truth and God and\Ndivinity are at the top of the chart and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.47,0:07:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is at the bottom of the chart.\NThe world
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the world has had it backwards for a\Nlong time. Still does.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a caveat before we start. If\Nyou're not dedicated to the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in the wrong lecture.\NIf you expect me to back up your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.28,0:07:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,favorite twisted positionalities, you're\Ngoing to be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to the way to the highest levels\Nof truth is often painful, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.47,0:07:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,anguishing. I went through it. So\Nthere's no point in whimpering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.68,0:08:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If I did it, you can do it.\NNobody was more dedicated to the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,than I was.\NI was one of the world's most devout and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.68,0:08:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,devout atheists for many years.\NAnd uh
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,all right. So sometimes the way the\Ntruth means going through
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,disillusionment of vested interests and\Nbelief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and one has to be willing to sacrifice\Neverything for the truth. Parts of your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.84,0:08:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,body may even disappear.\NStrange things may happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.68,0:08:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another person who sacrificed\Nthe feast of his body and we four of us
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.91,0:08:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,got together one time. Uh some kind of\Noath we took in some lifetime. Therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.48,0:08:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I recommend people don't take oaths you\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:09:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,or at least calibrate them before you\Ntake them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.16,0:09:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So what we stumbled upon the\Ncondition which prevailed which came
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.51,0:09:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,upon this entity standing before you\Nwas
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.39,0:09:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophic.\Ncatastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The degree of catastrophe was sort of\Nlike falling out of a 10-ft building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.44,0:09:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And the when you hit the ground, it was\Nsomething of that equivalence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.51,0:09:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is the absolute, the certain,\Nthe profound, the supreme
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.95,0:09:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,reveals itself in a stunning\Noverwhelming shock that leaves you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,silent for many years.\NThe way to that state then is what we
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.00,0:09:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have on the board.\NWe had on the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.80,0:10:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes you through the various states\Nwhich we recapitulate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here have never been to\Na lecture here or a lecture any of my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.24,0:10:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures? How many people have never\Nread power versus force? Get their names
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and addresses and\Nget their fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.04,0:10:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAll right. So, we won't spend too much
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.36,0:10:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,time recapitulating, but every time we\Ngo over it, we see something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.80,0:10:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The gravity of the ego is severe\Nand we see the reason for it. We can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.32,0:10:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lessen its hold on us by merely\Nunderstanding the evolution of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it arose.\NAnd so we recapitulate now each lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.07,0:10:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it's very useful\Nhow to contextualize the ego so as to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.76,0:10:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,avoid getting polarized about it. So as\Nto avoid get seeing as good good versus
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.16,0:11:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,evil, the good versus the bad. So\Nto transcend that's a very difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.07,0:11:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,duality to transcend. See because the\Nthe mind creates positionalities and now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a duality to transcend. And\Nthose traditionally are the dragons that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.44,0:11:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,stand in and guard the the gates of\Ntruth. each one of them represents. So I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.36,0:11:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to teach things backwards. Now I\Nstart with the end and go to the front
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.64,0:11:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that saves a lot of time.\NSo if we look at how the ego trans began
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.51,0:11:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,then when we get to that place of\Nsurrendering it the ego already has has
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.83,0:11:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,diminished in stature. And so\Nwe see that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.51,0:12:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all things come into manifestation\Nas a consequence of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality becoming actuality.\NThat action then by intention the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.44,0:12:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality becomes an actuality\Nbecause of the power of the infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.60,0:12:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,field. The field is so powerful that\Nthat which has potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.16,0:12:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,as life then comes into actuality.\NTherefore, creation and evolution are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.60,0:12:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,one and the same thing.\NEvolution is nothing but the witnessing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of potentiality coming into actuality.\NAnd we call that creation which seems to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.72,0:12:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind to the ego as sequential.\NThe only sequence is one of observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no sequence in the world as it\Nis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.76,0:13:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of a huge galaxy, I hope this is\Nthe right ear I'm poking in. Yes, this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.36,0:13:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,one has a thing in it.\NHave to get used to all this astronaut
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.95,0:13:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,equipment. So the um here's this molten\Nball. Energy E= MC². What does that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.76,0:13:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,mean? In just kindergarten language,\Nenergy can be converted to mass. They
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,can energy and mass can convert back and\Nforth from one to the other. That will
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.60,0:13:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,blow the mind of every physicist in the\Naudience. But roughly that's what it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.95,0:13:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,means.\NYou need time and various other things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.20,0:13:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the equation. But as a matter of\Nexperience, then this molten glob of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.95,0:13:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lava spins off from some galaxy,\Nspins around out there in space for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.20,0:13:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,eons, billions and billions, maybe even\Ntrillions of years and slowly cools
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.39,0:14:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,down. And as it cools down, its surface\Nnow becomes solidified.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.44,0:14:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The center of this world is still molten\Nlava. Center of this world is still
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.76,0:14:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,molten lava. So we we live on this\Ncooled off crust then. So as this lava
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,cools off it forms a crust that you can\Nstand on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can walk on. And in the\Nbeginning then the radiance of the power
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.07,0:14:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite field of consciousness\Ncell itself a quality of divinity as it
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.92,0:14:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,interacts with matter potentiates the\Nemergence of life. So the potentiality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.00,0:14:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for life is universal throughout\Nall of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.92,0:14:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,only awaiting proper conditions. H I\Nnever said that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.36,0:14:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Um that was correct. Okay. So does life\Nexist on other planets? Well, if the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.92,0:14:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality for life is universal,\Nthen it emerges as life wherever
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.56,0:15:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions are appropriate.\NHm. So then life emerged first on this
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.51,0:15:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,planet\Nin the most primitive form
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.56,0:15:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and it began as\Nthe first conscious entity was a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.56,0:15:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,bacteria\Nbefore we have a slide on that later but
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.12,0:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we won't go there yet.\NThe first matter, living matter was
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.92,0:15:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,lychans\Nand uh viruses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Viruses reproduce their DNA, but they're\Nnot conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.32,0:15:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't ask me why they're not conscious.\NI don't know why they're not conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.76,0:15:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A virus just doesn't know anything.\NBacteria somehow has the capacity to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.00,0:15:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.\NYeah. Is that the differential? Oh, so
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the virus does not have the capacity for\Nexperience. the bacteria literally
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.92,0:15:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences.\NWow. So, we discover new things all the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.00,0:16:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NI wondered why that was. So, I guess you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be a virus for a while. You move\Nup to being a bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.72,0:16:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, when you get to be a bacteria,\Nyou get to be experiential. Ah,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.07,0:16:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectivity emerges along with life.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.32,0:16:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Concomatant. With the emergency of life\Nemerges the capacity for subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.36,0:16:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NFor life to survive, it has to be able
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to get\Nit doesn't have innate within itself a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.07,0:16:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,source of energy.\NIt has to get it out there somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.88,0:16:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The amoeba doesn't have sufficient\Nenergy to survive. The ambia amieba has
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.72,0:16:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to go out and eat a crumb or whatever\Namieba eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.88,0:17:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Graham cracker crumb if I was an amoeba.\NSo you see that innate quality to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.95,0:17:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all it has to have appropriate\Nconditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's important to understand too\Nbecause everything
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.48,0:17:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,manifests as a result of of conditions.\NPropensity becomes actuality but only
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.52,0:17:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when conditions are appropriate.\NTherefore the intrinsic quality of life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then in the first beginning of\Nsubjectivity
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.24,0:17:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is getting gettingness.\NNothing has within it sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.16,0:17:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is self-powered.\NIt's got to get it from somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.60,0:17:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So right from the beginning, life at\Nleast from a human viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.64,0:17:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is a gettingness, a wantingness, a\Nhaving to have this in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:18:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we come on up through evolution\Nthen to the evolutionary series you see
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.88,0:18:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,increasing complexity and expertise in\Ngetting this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.64,0:18:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,h to survive. You have to be able to\Nacquire
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to get\Nand if you got to have the capacity to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.40,0:18:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,get then gettingness becomes intrinsic\Nto the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.20,0:18:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, you begin to worry that you might\Nnot have enough. That's what this when
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.72,0:18:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to the level of squirrel, the\Nsquirrel starts worrying there won't be
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.76,0:18:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,enough this winter. So, he starts\Ncreating wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.24,0:18:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wealth. The squirrel is the first\Ncapitalist. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.88,0:18:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal kingdom is full of\Ncapitalists who fill their burrows with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,food for the winter.\NI once watched a squirrel do that. In
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.55,0:18:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,fact, what I'm talking about this\Nmorning really came from observing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.12,0:18:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,animals. Uh, I once had a a bunch of\Nnuts left over from Christmas. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.84,0:19:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind that you're supposed to crack,\Nbut you never do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.03,0:19:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by June or July, the dust on them.\NSo, I take take the bowl of nuts and I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.40,0:19:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,put it out on in the grass. And I looked\Nout later and a squirrel went cuckoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You never saw a squirrel just freak out.\Nran excitedly here, there, the other
