Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.40,0:35:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the consequence of somebody's ego uh\Nwanting to control the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.68,0:36:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if a person wants to think what they\Nwant to think, why does the whole world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.04,0:36:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have to agree with you? You know what I\Nmean? You can see that's megalomaniac
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.20,0:36:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,just to begin with. Take a religious\Nposition that either the whole world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.96,0:36:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,agrees with you or you kill them all.\NWahabism
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.24,0:36:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is a variant\Nof Islamic culture. You know he the the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.44,0:36:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,birther of that was born about 300 years\Nago. He calibrates 30. No he calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.16,0:36:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,20. Wahabism calibrates about 30. And\Nthat position is the only ones that are
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.76,0:36:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,right are them which condemns all of\Nmankind except their cult.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.52,0:36:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All of mankind.\Nall of mankind declares other Islamics
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.16,0:36:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to be.\NSo that's egomania
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.44,0:37:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that only us are right and everybody\Nelse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.16,0:37:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say, well, what about just if\Neverybody else just didn't agree with
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.48,0:37:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you? No. If they don't agree with you,\Nthey must die.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.35,0:37:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the obligation to kill infidants.\NThat's what the war is about. People
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.04,0:37:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "What's the war about?" It's about\Nbeing seen as unworthy of life because
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.11,0:37:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't agree with a specific cult.\NThat's the whole story. The rest of it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.83,0:37:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is just the consequences of that.\NSo, we see what power the ego has in the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.07,0:37:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,really non-spiritual world.\NFinally, a person gets off of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.52,0:37:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Gets off of pride. gets off of pride and\Nbegins to listen to a different
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.44,0:37:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,intuitive\Nknowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.72,0:37:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and crosses over the level of 200. They\Nstop looking for blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.96,0:38:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is a consequence of that\Nwhich I am is a profound truth. When you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.83,0:38:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,get away from\Nwhen you get away from causality, when
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.24,0:38:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you get away from perpetrator and\Nvictim, when you get away from blame,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.72,0:38:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then you start owning your own\Nresponsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.96,0:38:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You give up on the excuses.\NYou whimper a little bit, but you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.59,0:38:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,really believe it.\NJust for appearance sake, you whimper,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.52,0:38:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but actually within yourself, you have\Nthe courage to face the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.20,0:38:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a difficult step. That's a\Ndifficult step.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.40,0:38:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,85% of the world totally is unable to\Nmake that step as yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.20,0:38:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In America, 51% now have cali now\Ncalibrate over 200. It was 5050.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.40,0:39:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,51%\Nof Americans
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.96,0:39:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate over 200. That's the first\Ntime in human history. First time in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.24,0:39:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,human history such a phenomena has ever\Noccurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.24,0:39:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That there's a predominance of people\Nwho calibrate at the level of truth or
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.48,0:39:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,over. It's never happened before.\NThat should create a good deal of upset
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.72,0:39:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere.\NThe truth is not popular. The truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.64,0:39:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not popular.\NPopularity is one thing. Truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.56,0:39:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,another.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.20,0:39:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This level of truth then shows a shift\Nin the basic energy of life. It's taking
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.56,0:39:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on a different dimension. It's going\Noutside of itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.44,0:39:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going out of outside of itself to\Nanother kind of knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.64,0:40:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The bacteria doesn't know anything about\Ntruth. Neither does a squirrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.00,0:40:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is what it is. Therefore, it's\Nneither good nor evil. It just is what
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.16,0:40:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it is. The nature of life as it emerges\Nthroughout
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.59,0:40:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution is intrinsically\Nself-directed. Uh all right. So the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.59,0:40:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,can now be turned around against itself\Nbecause the ego now can begin to desire
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.64,0:40:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual awareness,\Nself-improvement classes, the great
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.04,0:40:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,cultural creatives which are now 25% of\Nthe population.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.44,0:40:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-improvement classes are well\Nattended. So s now suddenly a a new
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.59,0:40:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,emergence. At first the ego grabs on to\Nthis.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.40,0:40:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In history, of course, religion has been\Nthe source of the greatest truth
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.32,0:40:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,available to mankind.\NThe only difficulty with
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.48,0:41:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sharing religious truths with the ego is\Nis that you end up with a spiritualized
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.56,0:41:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,ego. Yeah.\NThen you end up with the downside of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.96,0:41:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Christianity in the middle ages and etc.\NThat is the consequence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.59,0:41:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritualized ego\Nwhich can be brutally dangerous. In
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.20,0:41:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,fact, the most dangerous thing on the\Nplanet is the spiritualized ego. That is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.16,0:41:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the most dangerous thing on the planet.\NThat's what the current world conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.28,0:41:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is about.\NIf you don't agree with us, you must all
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.16,0:41:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,die.\NThat's a little selfish when you think
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.68,0:41:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to it. A little bit selfish. Anyway,\Nyeah. All right. So, one thing that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.35,0:41:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,happens when you have the capacity to\Ntell the truth is the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.44,0:42:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I could be wrong.\NMaybe I could be wrong. That never
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.16,0:42:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs below 200.\Nbelow 200, it's somebody else's fault,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.28,0:42:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but not my fault.\NTherefore, I respect any politician who
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.96,0:42:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,says, you know, I screwed up.\NSo, you wonder why people stonewall
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.59,0:42:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,when admitting the truth would be so\Neasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.35,0:42:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you know? So, you forgot to to get bread\Non the way home. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.40,0:42:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the beginning of the\Nbloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.28,0:42:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Most domestic battles, you see the\Npictures of the people with with the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.83,0:42:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,black eye,\Netc. That's the way it started. It
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.88,0:42:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,started, you forgot to fill the gas\Ntank. You forgot to get the bread. You
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.68,0:43:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,forgot to mill the letter.\NAnd then it escalates from there. Why
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.31,0:43:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,would it escalate over something so\Ntrivial? Because the ego, in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.68,0:43:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,survive, has to feel that it's right.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.16,0:43:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for somebody to admit that they were\Nwrong is impossible below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.72,0:43:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to not get your feelings hurt, I\Nguarantee I'll give you a perfect list
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.35,0:43:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure your feelings never get\Nhurt again.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.83,0:43:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a legalized pad.\NWrite down all your faults.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.35,0:43:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Write down your faults that other people\Nthink you have, even though you think
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.48,0:43:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they're liars.\NAnd now own them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.28,0:43:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they see you that way and you're\Nnot that way, you take responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.83,0:43:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that because of you, you they see you\Nthat way. What about you is allowing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.40,0:44:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,them to see you that way. See, you just\Npresume that there's some degree of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.28,0:44:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,truth in all of it. If you're a liar,\Nyou tell them, "I'm the best liar on the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.35,0:44:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,planet. You want to hire me? I'm worth a\Nfortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.96,0:44:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I forgetful?\NIf this wasn't connected to this, I
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.11,0:44:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,would have lost it a long time ago."\NIf you own your possible downside, don't
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.96,0:44:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see? Nobody has any place to attack\Nyou.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.64,0:44:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And people intuit it where you've got a\Nand that's what they go for. So if
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.16,0:44:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're being abused by people in various\Nways, it's because you're attracting it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.07,0:44:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,by something you're not owning about\Nyourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.48,0:44:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, there's nothing wrong with\Nbeing stupid and ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.52,0:44:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm stupid and ugly, right?\NI was on a radio show in Chicago with a
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.24,0:45:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,well-known jock there and one of his\Nteam admits he's stupid and ugly. In
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.28,0:45:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,fact, the part he plays on the program\Nis when you need somebody stupid and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.88,0:45:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,ugly, he comes in and makes a stupid and\Nugly comment and they all cheer. Thank
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.16,0:45:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you. He says,\Nhe makes a very good living being stupid
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.28,0:45:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and ugly.\NSo we admit our faults and we stop
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.31,0:45:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,labeling them faults.\NI mean they used to call me shorty.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.48,0:45:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I get indignant and be sensitive?\NProtest
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.83,0:45:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shorty. H.\NSo we have to get over narcissistic
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.40,0:45:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sensitivity. People who are made\Nuncomfortable by things need a
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.56,0:45:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist.\NAnd the best advice is to get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.64,0:45:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If the word God over the courthouse\Nmakes you nervous, you better see your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.56,0:46:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,analyst about it. You know what I mean?\NI mean, those three words are not coming
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.72,0:46:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,down off the cement and hitting you in\Nthe head or something. What what is it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.68,0:46:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doing to you?\NAll negative reactions are then not
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.16,0:46:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,caused from outside. It's how you\Nchoose. Everybody who's uncomfortable in
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.04,0:46:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,various situations is completely legally\Nfree to not feel uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.31,0:46:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm trying to explain to them how to\Ndo it. The world is not going to agree
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.11,0:46:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with your political views. So\Nthe world is not going to agree with
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.56,0:46:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,many things you hold about yourself.\NThe way to become bulletproof
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.56,0:46:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is to own any negativity that you can\Neven imagine might apply to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.76,0:46:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when you go to accept that, you'll\Nrun into the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.04,0:46:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are dumb and ugly. Well, that's\Ntrue.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.56,0:46:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But God loves me.\NGod loves me anyway. Okay. You're short
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.40,0:47:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and stubby and you wear thick glasses,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.83,0:47:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The coach wouldn't approve me for the\Nteam. Any team.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.40,0:47:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The the chess. He suggested chess.\NI remember he squeezed my bones and he
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.07,0:47:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,says\None quarterback hits you with that and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.83,0:47:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's busted. So even with all these\Nthings my mom bought me or I bought
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.24,0:47:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,myself helmets and all this crap, you\Nknow, and all these pads and all they
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.00,0:47:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't let me out on the field.\NYeah. I went back to trying to climb a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.59,0:47:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,rope loses all the way to the ceiling. I\Nwould get about this far and I go with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.24,0:47:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NThat just wasn't my world. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.64,0:47:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see how you accept your\Nlimitation? What is your world? Well, if
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.80,0:47:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you got four eyes and you're skinny and\Nand look like some kind of comical
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.24,0:47:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,character, you can sit in a big book and\Nread Plato's Republic, which is what I
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.48,0:48:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,did.\NSocrates. So, my hero was Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.52,0:48:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates, right?\N>> What?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.28,0:48:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, this is a pointer.\NWell, okay. There's the pointer. A
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.72,0:48:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pointer is whatever you call a pointer.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.72,0:48:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature, the quality of the ego then\Nis for survival. It believes it has to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.83,0:48:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly get because it thinks that\Nthe source of his life of its
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.76,0:48:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,its life is out there and has to be\Ngotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.88,0:48:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This delusion, this illusion persists\Nall the way up the scale. All the way up
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.00,0:48:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the scale until you begin to experience\Na different energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.40,0:48:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what brings in what you need is who\Nyou are. As you're a friendly person,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.68,0:49:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to notice everybody smiles at\Nyou. Everybody smiles at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.72,0:49:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost everybody smiled at me this\Nmorning when I was greeting everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.00,0:49:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Couple of people looked at me a little\Nlike we'll wait and see, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.31,0:49:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, okay.\NAll right. So, who you become then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.31,0:49:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to have an effect beyond\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.24,0:49:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh because now you're beginning to live\Nin a different field. So, we're getting
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.16,0:49:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,out of cause and effect. We're getting\Nout of the ego and we're seeing that who
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.64,0:49:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we are is now determining a field. And\Nthe experiences of the field are
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.07,0:49:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,different than what they were. So the\Nfield that calibrates at 200 is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.76,0:49:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,different than the field and different\Nthan the field at 350.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.11,0:49:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,350.\NWhether people like it or not. I always
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.04,0:49:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,say, you know, Walmart calibrates at\N350, 365.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.64,0:50:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If that makes you mad, see your doctor.\NIt makes you mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.59,0:50:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact. It does calibrate that.\NAll right. So, what we discovered then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.96,0:50:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was a way of um\Ncalibrating the level of truth. We
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.48,0:50:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered that everything below 200\Nmakes you weak. Everything over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.92,0:50:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,makes you go strong. We now had for the\Nfirst time in human history a means of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.96,0:50:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,discerning truth from falsehood. plus a\Nmeans of discerning what is truth which
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.16,0:50:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we found out you cannot define what\Ntruth is without stating the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.88,0:50:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is only true within a certain\Ncontext. And we saw why the world was
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.44,0:50:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to reach any agreement on what is\Ntruth since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.96,0:50:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been no common agreement on what\Nis truth. As we'll see later,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.40,0:50:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see now down here. If you don't\Nget, you're going to die. up here. What
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.16,0:50:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you need begins to appear of its own.\NAnd I experimented with that when I did
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.35,0:51:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,first did the course of miracles. It\Nsays you don't need anything out there
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.31,0:51:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at all. So I walked out of the house\Nwith no money, no food or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.80,0:51:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure enough, around lunch time, somebody\NI was passing by said, "Do you have
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.28,0:51:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,lunch yet?" I said, "No." He says, "I\Ngot an extra sandwich." Everything began
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.44,0:51:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to appear of its own out of nothingness,\Nout of nowhere, just like chocolate
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.68,0:51:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,appears now, you know, by the box.\NI don't ask any chocolate. It just
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.80,0:51:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,appears, you know, have a closet full of\Nchocolate. So
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.31,0:51:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what you become then begins to influence\Nthe field. And what you need, what you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.59,0:51:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,need, what you really need then becomes\Na present by virtue of the quality of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.24,0:51:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the field itself.\NThis is beyond the ego's understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.16,0:51:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego cannot understand why morality,\Nfairness, ethics, integrity etc. is not
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.96,0:51:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a sacrifice.\NPeople below 200 think those are sacri
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.52,0:52:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a sacrifice and there is a very\Nverbal viciferous
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.64,0:52:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,group out there that wants to vilify\Nmorality and ethics and all because it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.04,0:52:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't see any gain in it. Doesn't see\Nany gain. Doesn't see any gain. No,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.35,0:52:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no immediate gain of visible to\Nthe ego. And it's only by being that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.80,0:52:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,being that that you discover\Nwhat it means
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.55,0:52:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,without looking for anything. You're\Nsitting in a chair and your spouse puts
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.72,0:52:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,their hands on your shoulders and you\Nfeel the world is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.40,0:52:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The kitty sits on your lap and purr.\NWhat more do you need? You're complete
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.52,0:52:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and total from instant to instant. Then\Nit dawns on you one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.83,0:52:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,H then when you stop coming from lack,\Nyou see when you come from lack, when
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.40,0:53:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at the Newtonian paradigm, it\Nlooks like uh you go from incomplete to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.16,0:53:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,complete to incomplete to complete and\Nyou begin to realize that you really go
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.24,0:53:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from complete to complete.\NThis instant is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.20,0:53:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This instant is complete. Is there\Nanything I need at this instant? No, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.35,0:53:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,complete.\NYou go from complete from incomp instead
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.88,0:53:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of from incomplete which is the world of\Nthe ego which is a wantingness. You
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.28,0:53:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,always feel incomplete to complete to\Ncomplete. Doesn't mean you can't have
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.55,0:53:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,more\Nbut you don't feel any suffering that it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.72,0:53:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't yet. Huh? Because what you want\Npeople want to know what is the clue to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.44,0:53:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,success? The clue to success is to just\Nbe exactly what you are. Be a class act.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.16,0:53:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Be completely and totally\N100% what you are and the world will
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.72,0:53:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,provide all that you need.\NWho's my favorite?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.52,0:53:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Satcho, right?\N>> Yeah. Satcho.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.07,0:54:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Louis Armstrong. Well, we\Ncalibrated Lemstrong. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.83,0:54:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just wonderfully being precisely who you\Nare. Absolutely. you know, sends people
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.20,0:54:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,into joy.\NSends people into joy. He just he
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.28,0:54:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 500. You know, sort of a\Nuniversal lovingness, but it comes from
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.07,0:54:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,not wanting anything but sharing who one\Nis with the world. To share who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.52,0:54:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,completely with the world, then you're\Ncomplete and total. Need nothing. Need
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.44,0:54:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing from the world. So these\Nfeelings down here don't keep recurring.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.72,0:54:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want anything, you can't be\Ndisappointed. Because you're complete in
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.11,0:54:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,total from moment to moment. Huh? So\Nlife becomes perfect from moment to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.00,0:54:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,moment.\NTherefore we can stop vilifying the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.20,0:54:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and see it as an evol evolutionary\Narrest. So below 200 what you see is an
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.20,0:55:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary arrest in which the animal\Nemotions the animal state tends to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.68,0:55:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,predominate.\NThen you get the emergence of the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.59,0:55:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual and then you have that\Ndifficult period in spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.35,0:55:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're looking at the downside.\NYou're looking at angriness. You're
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.48,0:55:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at selfishness and you're being\Npulled up towards the top and all this
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.59,0:55:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,stuff is now being pulled up in the\Nunconscious. You know, there's various
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.44,0:55:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,archetypes. So you can clear out one\Narchetype and then another one comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.83,0:55:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all the, you know, comes up.\NYeah. The one I had the most problem was
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.80,0:55:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual knight who was always\Ngetting indignant
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.40,0:55:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,at\Nnon-integrity. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.72,0:55:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're going to get indignant and\Nnon- integrity, you're going to spend a
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.28,0:55:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of time being indignant.\NYou know, shock how a person could say
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.68,0:55:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that under these circumstances. You say\Nit's not possible. It's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.64,0:56:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. To get over judgmentalism\Nthen is to accept that the world is the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.20,0:56:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,way it is because it serves a tremendous\Npurpose being that way. It's a great
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.40,0:56:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic opportunity to be born in this\Nworld which is in my view of it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.92,0:56:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,purgatorial in that it goes from the\Nvery bottom to the very highest. And the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.59,0:56:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddhist said fortunate one is\Nto have been born a human being. even
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.83,0:56:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,more fortunate\Nuh to have heard of enlightenment and
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.40,0:56:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,even rarer still to seek enlightenment\Nand most rare of all to have achieved
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.31,0:56:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it. So we become grateful for our human\Nexistence instead of be bewailing it. So
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.11,0:56:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gratitude takes us right over 200 to\Nbegin with. If this is a world of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.48,0:56:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,maximum opportunity for spiritual growth\Nand development, then there's some part
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.35,0:57:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of us should be saying, well, God, I got\Nmy doubts, but I give thanks that this
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.07,0:57:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is a world in which I can experience and\Ngrow, where I have freedom of the will.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.11,0:57:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one's consciousness level is set by\Nthe spiritual will.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.79,0:57:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're constantly presented with yes, no,\Nyes, no. If you watch the intricacy of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.96,0:57:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind's operations, which I don't\Nadvise, but if you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.20,0:57:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that it's saying yes, no every\Ninstant. Every instant, it's really
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.52,0:57:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,making a decision. It's really\Noverwhelming that it's able to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.79,0:57:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does it nonverbally and\Nnon-linguistically.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.28,0:57:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, the arm moves out of its\Nown. Something decided to move the arm
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.11,0:57:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its own.\Nyou weren't even thinking about it. All
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.88,0:57:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,right? So then you run eventually into\Nspontaneity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.04,0:57:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to realize everything is\Nhappening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.00,0:58:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go to the slide. Has anybody\Ngot any questions about this? Uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.24,0:58:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,next book I'm going to do will go into\Neach one of these more specifically how
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.07,0:58:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend each level. Uh the next\Nbook is going to be written, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.04,0:58:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,almost completely for the spiritual\Naspirant. The one I'm finishing now is
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.11,0:58:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,using the calibrated levels of truth.\NYou know, using the calibration
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.96,0:58:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,technique, what what do you find if you\Nif you examine the whole world
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.11,0:58:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of history and all of\Nhuman conduct, political
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.24,0:58:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities,\Nuh possessions, uh movies. So, we'll do
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.20,0:58:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,movies later today. Uh we did 200 movies\Nand uh anyway, you don't have to copy
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.72,0:58:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,them down because they'll be on the\Nbook. All right. So, I'll move up. Move
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.83,0:58:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,up. I thought it was interesting because\Nmovies are very big in our in our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.40,0:58:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These are calibrated levels of\Nconsciousness which George Serinsky sent
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.55,0:58:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,us. Uh he recalculated the figures we\Nhad in the book. The figures I had in
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.83,0:59:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the book about the power of a loving\Nthought compared to a an unloving
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.88,0:59:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,thought is something like minus to the\N400 million
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.92,0:59:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,versus minus something or other. I'm not\Nvery good at math. So I just did it with
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.96,0:59:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology.\NThat's the way I figure out how much I
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.72,0:59:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,owe my secretary.\NWe say I owe you so much so much. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.20,0:59:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,how much I make the check for. Neither\None of us can figure it out. I know. All
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.00,0:59:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,right. So anyway, what George did was he\Nknows more about mathematics and he
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.35,0:59:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated the levels of consciousness\Nuh in microwatts with more advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.40,0:59:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,mathematics.\NAnd you see the how how it progresses
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.16,0:59:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,here up to the level of 100 then 200\Nsuddenly you see a major incline and at
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.55,0:59:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,500 you see a very major jump and at 600\Nof course you start going out to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.68,1:00:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,infinity.\NAll right so we'll go to the next 600 we
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.48,1:00:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,don't say too much about let's because\Nit's very rare. All right 250 here you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.52,1:00:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,here's 78% of the world's population.\NLet's see if that's still a fact because
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.48,1:00:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,these figures shift. We have permission\Nto ask that. Of the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.68,1:00:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,totally\N78% are below 200. Is this 79%.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.44,1:00:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,78%.\NAll right. So, it's like the temperature
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.79,1:00:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ocean doesn't change much over\Nthe eons. I don't suppose the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.48,1:00:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature of today's ocean is much\Ndifferent than a thousand years ago or
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.35,1:00:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,thousand years before.\NSo 78% of the world's population. See,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.04,1:00:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easy to do spiritual work if you\Nbegin to realize who you are, how you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.48,1:00:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be that way, and what is the\Ncontext in which you're trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.16,1:00:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplish what you're trying to\Naccomplish. You see, other than just
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.68,1:00:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,pick picking a a cute book off the\Nbookshelf and jumping into it, uh I
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.55,1:01:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,think it's useful to have a total\Ncontextualization of who you are under
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.83,1:01:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what circumstances, how the human\Ncondition got to be that way, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.16,1:01:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you're going to go someplace,\Nyou should know where you are on the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.79,1:01:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,map, you know, to start from. So, all\Nright. So, here's how it balances out.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.16,1:01:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If that is so, why doesn't the world\Nblow apart? It's because the 15% over
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.59,1:01:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,200 have so much power. This 15% has\Nenormous power because those are
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.68,1:01:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,logarithmic. The power of the 15%\Ntotally counterbalances the negativity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.88,1:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 85%.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.00,1:01:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise,\Nthat which hates all of human life, you
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.52,1:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know, that which wants to destroy all of\Nhuman life except its own little band of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.00,1:01:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people,\Nif you state the truth about it, it
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.44,1:01:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,hates human life.\NH never thought of that. The energy of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.48,1:01:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which I'm thinking that's coming out\Npolitically hates human life. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.64,1:02:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hates human life. Not just infidels.\NHates human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.20,1:02:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know what it's up to? It\Nhates you in life. And all it does is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.64,1:02:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,find some rationale to work to express\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.83,1:02:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But the hatred there is primary, not\Nsecondary.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.79,1:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The hatred there is primary.\NIt's primary, folks. Not something you
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.79,1:02:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,did, not something America did, not\Nsomething George Bush did, not something
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.40,1:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Iranians did,\Nnot something that the oil cartel did.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.00,1:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They are that way and then they find a\Nrationale to make it seem plausible and
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.72,1:02:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,get followers.\NIt's like you start out hating somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.83,1:02:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you find reasons and excuses to\Njustify it. Well, her hair looks funny
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.07,1:03:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and her nose is wide and her feet are\Ntoo fat. I mean, now you start
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.44,1:03:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the truth is you started out with\Nhate. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.16,1:03:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to cross over 200, you would have to own\Nthat you started with hate and now
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.55,1:03:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you're just trying to justify it, find\Nreasons for expression, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.44,1:03:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But the hatred was there primary. Let's\Ndo that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.79,1:03:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The hatred we're experiencing in the\Nworld today preexisted.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.16,1:03:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Pre-existed all the phenomena exist.\NIt preexisted all the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.88,1:03:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's that solves a lot of things,\Ndoesn't it? It pre-existed. Pre-existed.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.59,1:03:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So we have a dualistic ego\Nwhich we've just talked about before
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.96,1:03:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that tends to separate things into good\Nand evil. That's the other trouble with
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.07,1:03:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated levels of consciousness\Nis the mind tends to think about the
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.00,1:04:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,good is 200 and over and the bad is 200\Nbelow. And that is a problem you do have
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.55,1:04:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to transcend. Yes,\Nit isn't that it's good versus evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.68,1:04:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that which is more evolved in\Ncontrast to that which is less evolved.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.55,1:04:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that which calibrates at 35\Nwhich was present as life on this
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.52,1:04:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,planet. The\Nthe age of the reptiles,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.24,1:04:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the Komodo dragon\Nhistorically still exists. It didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.16,1:04:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,disappear and get replaced by something\Nbetter. It's still here. Still here.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.59,1:04:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAll right. So we don't want to say this
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.44,1:04:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is good this is bad. So how should we\Nsee it? We'll see things are more
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.79,1:04:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved or less evolved. The only one\Nthing that is on the calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.68,1:04:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is degree of evolution.\NThe degree of evolution up goes up this
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.55,1:04:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,way or down this way. So we see that 85%\Nof the people on the planet have not
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.59,1:05:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,evolved to the point of the willingness\Nto own the truth. Huh? Honesty,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.79,1:05:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity, huh? The courage to face the\Ntruth.
