Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.11,1:05:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,common. We should get some new slides\Nbecause you've seen some of these
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.07,1:05:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,before. And that is the presence or the\Nabsence of heat. There's not heat versus
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.03,1:05:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,cold. There's either heat and there's\Nvarying degrees of heat. This is lots of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.76,1:05:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,heat and this is less heat. But they're\Nnot opposites. This is desiraability.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.72,1:05:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This you really want it a lot. You say\Nit's precious. And if you think it's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.16,1:05:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,ugly, you call it call it awful. Huh?\NThen the mind makes the mistake of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.03,1:05:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,rejecting it into the world and saying\Nit is awful. No, you see it as awful. It
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.35,1:05:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is neither awful nor not awful. So the\Nbig mistake the ego makes is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.88,1:05:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to confuse rest interna with rest\Nexterna. the Latin for
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.59,1:06:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is within the mind and that\Nwhich is in nature in the world and to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.64,1:06:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,confuse that how I see it is how the\Nworld is how you see it is how you see
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.07,1:06:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it you should stop there\Nthe false is to say therefore that's the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.68,1:06:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,way the world is no okay I see something\Nas such so if you own that then you're
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.07,1:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous is if you jump and say because\NI see it that way that's the way the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.28,1:06:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,world is that is not onism. All right.\NSo that distinction of course is very
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.59,1:06:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,famous in philosophic history. All\Nright. So the next one we got is
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.83,1:06:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,desiraability. Again we say it's\Nheavenly. It's wonderful. So, we look at
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.48,1:06:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated scale of consciousness\Njust like we do every night's TV news
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.68,1:06:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we say, "Isn't that horrible? Isn't\Nthat ghastly? Isn't that wicked? Isn't
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.55,1:07:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that bad? And isn't this person\Nwonderful? And this is good. This is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.00,1:07:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,very good."\NSo, that judgmentalism then is a
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.16,1:07:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,projection is a projection. Oh, you got\Nit to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.31,1:07:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is a projection of the ego.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.52,1:07:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Psychoanalysis, you know,\Nis one place you learn that quickly. You
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.35,1:07:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,know, the theorists who reject\Npsychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.72,1:07:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them, "Yeah, right. You go lay\Ndown an analyst couch an hour hour a
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.31,1:07:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,day, five days a week for a couple years\Nand see what comes up."
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.68,1:07:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't think you got an\Nunconscious, so
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.79,1:07:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,things are seen as heavenly, very good.\NThese are all projections.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.11,1:07:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing that happens\Nwhen you go to lay down on the analyst
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.28,1:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,couch is instantly because he just sits\Nthere and says nothing. He's not saying
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.00,1:08:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,anything. Got a pad of paper just like\Nin the cartoon. How many people have
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.40,1:08:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,been in psychoanalysis?\NYeah. Okay. You know, he just lays
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.55,1:08:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there. You just leave there and uh\Ninstantly you find it's difficult to
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.28,1:08:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,talk. You're wondering what he thinks\Nabout you. You presume he's thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.83,1:08:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this. He thinks you're stupid. If I say\Nthis, he's going to think I'm six
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.12,1:08:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,pervert. I mean, you know, all the crap\Ncomes up like this. People say they
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.71,1:08:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,don't believe in psychoanalysis. I say,\N"Yeah, right. You need a doctor."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.35,1:08:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, one one value is you're getting\Nover you get over being judgmental
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.27,1:08:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because you see it comes out of like\Nnowhere. It's like instinctual. You
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.19,1:08:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't even know this guy and already you\Ngot a whole program you're projecting on
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.40,1:08:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to him. He won't like me because of so\Nand so, uh, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.35,1:08:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The other duality is light versus dark.\NSo once once we get this principle down,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.40,1:08:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to replace these slides, but\NI use these out of town. So
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.27,1:09:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,either light is very There's a lot of\Nlight up at the top or light is absent.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.64,1:09:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is no such thing as light and\Ndarkness being opposites.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.67,1:09:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like nonspace has no existence.\NIt's important to the kinesiologic test
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.23,1:09:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because what the test merely tests is\Nwhether a thing is true. That's all. It
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.35,1:09:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't test true versus false. It only\Ntests true.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.00,1:09:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the light either goes on or the light\Ndoes not go on. So if what I'm holding
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.40,1:09:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in mind and I don't have to tell it to\Nher verbally, I don't have to tell her
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.19,1:09:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,verbally what I'm holding in mind. I can\Njust say what I'm holding in mind is
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.96,1:09:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,true or calibrates over 200. That's how\Nthe test is done.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.15,1:09:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the people who do the tests\Nhave themselves have to calibrate 200 or
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.64,1:09:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,over and the intention intention of the\Nquestion has to be integrous. So you
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.40,1:10:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,can't use it for, you know, self-s\Nserving needs. When I wrote par's first,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.23,1:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought everybody could use it. I was\Nvery naive at the time. I thought, oh my
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.52,1:10:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,god, everybody, everybody can use it.\NAnd then I discovered, no, that is not
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.84,1:10:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so. It's only the people who have\Nalready committed themselves to wanting
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.15,1:10:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to know the truth for its own sake. So\Nthe willingness to let go of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.92,1:10:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,positionality\Nand instead align oneself with truth
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.52,1:10:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,takes one rapidly to God rapidly.\NAll right. So we said that the mind all
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.80,1:10:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,right we did the mind before. The mind\Nthen is the field in which all this uh
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.52,1:10:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothesis goes on. So the ego then\Nbegins to dominate not just feelings but
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.28,1:10:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,our thoughts about things.\NThe way to overcome and transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.80,1:11:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings then is to let go the\Npositionality which underlies a
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.32,1:11:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,particular feeling. And we find that\Nfeelings are linked together. You're
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.96,1:11:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,angry when you say well why am I angry?\NI'm angry because I was insulted. Well
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.67,1:11:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's pride right?\NAnd why was I was insulted? Because I
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.71,1:11:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,expected to be applauded or agreed with\Nand I wasn't. So that was looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.23,1:11:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,gain, wanting everybody to agree with\Nyou. And that is coming from control. So
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.28,1:11:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how they're all linked together.\NTherefore, you can unravel the ego like
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.15,1:11:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a sweater with a yarn. You just start\Npulling the yarn here and the whole ego
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.04,1:11:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,will disintegrate. The whole ego will\Ndisintegrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.80,1:11:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Its structure is not based on truth.\NBut on a fallacy that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.12,1:11:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the laws of life which dominated early\Nprimitive life in its earliest forms
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.76,1:12:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same law that humans have to live\Nby. They do up to 200 but beyond 200
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.88,1:12:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then they begin to transcend that. So\Nwe're here to escape the dominance of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.96,1:12:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego which is a characteristic of the\Nanimal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.80,1:12:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And I brought my animal with me again. I\Nalmost forgot my animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.80,1:12:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I advise everybody to have an animal\Nthat represents their ego, which is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.04,1:12:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,greedy. Yes. Selfish,\Nwants more, hates people,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.32,1:12:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,wants to get even.\NYour ego is doing what it's supposed to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.23,1:12:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,do. Folks, there's no point to feel\Nguilt about greed. It's doing what it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.36,1:12:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks it's supposed to do.\NThe squirrel's ego wants more and more
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.56,1:12:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nuts.\NTons of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.48,1:12:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If I brought in a truck and unloaded a\Nbunch of nuts, you know what the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.71,1:13:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,squirrel would do? He'd run all around\Nthe edge getting more nuts. He's got a
Dialogue: 0,1:13:00.40,1:13:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mountain of them.\NAll right, what's our next surprise?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.84,1:13:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh yeah. So now the mind gets taken over\Nbecause when the prefrontal cortex was
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.56,1:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,added, the animal brain was not removed.\NFolks, there you got the whole human
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.80,1:13:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,experience explained to you. The source\Nof all suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.12,1:13:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The old animal brain was not replaced by\Na prefrontal cortex. It was added on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.04,1:13:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're in a worse fix than you were\Nbefore.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.19,1:13:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You were just a happy lion eating\Nrabbits cuz he's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.52,1:13:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you got a problem. You're killing\Nthe rabbits. Oh my god.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.84,1:14:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't I be a vegetarian?\NPoor Eeyore.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.84,1:14:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyhow,\Nour affliction then the price of being a
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.92,1:14:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,human being, the price of the evolution\Nof consciousness is we go through a
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.67,1:14:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,period of tremendous conflict. To be a\Nhuman being is agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.36,1:14:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody disagree?\NI was going to say I'll refer you to my
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.56,1:14:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,analyst.\NIt's agonizing. Why? Because you've got
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.04,1:14:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a prefrontal cortex plastered onto an\Nold animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.12,1:14:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a conscience plastered onto a\Nbrain that wants to kill people.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.96,1:14:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NDon't you feel guilty?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.23,1:14:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NHe doesn't feel guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.04,1:15:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So see that the source of\Nyour guilt is a byproduct and a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.00,1:15:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of your own spiritual\Naspiration.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.40,1:15:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not intrinsic and innate to the act\Nor anything. Guilt is a super
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.92,1:15:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,superimposition that you project onto it\Nor you buy from society.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.80,1:15:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You made that up.\NThe tiger eats the rabbit because it's
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.56,1:15:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,hungry.\NThat's all. That's the world the way it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.84,1:15:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is. Rest external, rest internal. Now\Nyou've got a prefrontal cortex that
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.00,1:15:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,throws you into guilt. You just murdered\Nthe rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.48,1:15:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NThat keeps the mind very busy.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.88,1:15:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It keeps it going. So what happens is\Nthe ego's energy now gets invested in
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.64,1:15:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind. So when you look at your mind\Nnow what you're seeing is the energy of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.84,1:16:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the primitive ego\Nwhich for survival is now become a tool
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.28,1:16:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of the animal.\NYour mind is the tool of the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.32,1:16:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it's interested in what?\NSurvival.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.00,1:16:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind is up to the same thing as\Nany animal is up to.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.80,1:16:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's how it keeps going. It\Npoliticizes everything. That'll do you a
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.19,1:16:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of lifetimes. It moralizes about\Neverything. That'll get you a lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.80,1:16:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetimes. It idealizes everything.\NHypothesizes
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.60,1:16:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of hyp the hypothetical.\NIt romanticises, ranticize. It
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.96,1:16:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,criticizes.\NEmotionalizes, dramatizes,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.23,1:16:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophizes, victimizes. It\Nrationalizes. It makes endless excuses.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.92,1:16:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It lives in a fantasy world of\Ninfantilism.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.84,1:16:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it likes to intellectualize,\Nit likes to mentalize, it glamorizes
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.23,1:17:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,things,\Ndemonizes them, it prizes them as goals,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.00,1:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and it endlessly theorizes about things.\NThe hypothetical is the ego's
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.36,1:17:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,grandstanding through the intellect. So,\Nnext slide. We're going to go through
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.36,1:17:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the slides a little faster. We got to\Nwatch it because we got 200 movies to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.04,1:17:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,go. You know,\NI've lost track of time. What time do we
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.00,1:17:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,take a break?\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.60,1:17:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh?\N>> About 10:30.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.52,1:17:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What time is it now?\N>> 10 after 10.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.32,1:17:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> My good watch. I broke the crystal. Or\NGod broke the crystal. Somebody did.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.12,1:17:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody is to blame.\NHere we talk about the paradigms of the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.19,1:17:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Newtonian and quantum mechanics. We said\Nthat the ego then works on the basis of
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.28,1:17:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian paradigm of causality.\NThe way to jump the calibrate the the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.96,1:17:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,world of the 400s, the world of the\N400s, the Newtonian paradigm is the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.56,1:18:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,intellect, which becomes taken over by\Nthe ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.92,1:18:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, quick way to transcend the 400s\Nand not spend 20 lifetimes at it
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.76,1:18:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is to see, merely see. And if you don't\Nsee it, take my word for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.92,1:18:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing comes into to being as a result\Nof causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.80,1:18:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything comes into existence out of\Nnothingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.84,1:18:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All arises out of nothing as a\Npotentiality.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.80,1:18:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A potentiality within an infinite p\Npower field becomes an actuality by
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.28,1:18:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue of the power of the field.\NNot by virtue of that out there. Not by
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.80,1:18:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue of that out there potentiality\Nnow becomes an actuality and this is the
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.08,1:18:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what we call creation.\NThe unmanifest becomes manifest by
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.52,1:19:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue of the divinity of the infinite\Nfield
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.44,1:19:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call God.\NThat is an absolute fact. Is that is an
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.60,1:19:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute fact. Therefore, you really\Ndon't have to think anymore because now
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.36,1:19:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you got it.\NEverything is attracting to it what it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.52,1:19:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,attracts to it by virtue of what it is.\NWow. That totally changes how the you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.52,1:19:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see the world operating\Nblows a lot of sociological theories.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.48,1:19:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of that which you are\Nkarmically what you've inherited when
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.67,1:19:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you get born. Every being already has a\Ncalibrated level of energy at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.36,1:19:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of birth over these things that could be\Niffy. We that's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.52,1:19:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Every being at the moment of birth\Nalready has a calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.44,1:19:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,energy.\NIt's also born in the most optimal
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.67,1:20:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances propitious for karmic\Nevolution for the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.96,1:20:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. So we start from where we\Nleft off with the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.64,1:20:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. We start in this\Nphysicality.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.48,1:20:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We then attract to us\Nthat which we attract is because of our
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.23,1:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,own magnetism. Ah there you got it.\NSo the calibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.00,1:20:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then could be compared to magnetic\Npower. Huh? Those with weak power
